Thanks Nejc for facilitating further discussion on this.

Just to clarify the process for all concerned, the actual final point of approval for a BP is more the filing & approval of the corresponding blueprint in launchpad, as opposed to landing the spec in ceilometer-specs repo (as the former is the point at which it shows up on the release manager's radar).

For the moment, I'm going to:

* file a placeholder BP in launchpad
* leave the specification URL unset on that BP
* mark the LP BP as blocked pending the outcome of the extended discussion on the best approach to partitioning the central agent workload among horizontally scaled agents

Finally, just a gentle reminder that the urgency here is being driven by the looming juno-3 deadline, and the fact that we're way past the original spec acceptance deadline. So, expediting any review input on the re-proposed patch would be much appreciated! :)

Thanks!
Eoghan"}, {'account_id': 9562, 'date': '2014-08-05 11:09:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-05 11:09:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: -Verified

Revert "Central agent horizontal scaling spec"

This reverts commit 725a291e9c9ad1e6100f54735b2e13a64f123d13.

The initial commit was merged prematurely, before all of the
interested parties got a chance to review it. It will be
re-submitted as a fresh change.

Change-Id: Ib79af6ab62c0556511fc34f144411b5c174b8950

commit_message:
Mask block_device_info auth_password in virt driver debug logs

The block_device_info object can have an auth_password key which is
getting logged at debug level in several virt drivers so we need to
sanitize the message getting logged.

Adds tests to ensure the logged messages are properly sanitized.

Note that bug 1321785 was opened to track the long-term design issues
with storing the password in the block_device_info dict since this can
crop up elsewhere if it's logged.  The immediate fix here is to mask
what's already exposed.

Closes-Bug: #1319943

(cherry picked from commit 5dda3a6ab2becb5dd0b58c088f6daad807e12276)

Conflicts:

commit_message:
ofagent: Stop monitoring ovsdb for port changes

Perform dumb polling instead.
Now ofagent port monitoring is mostly ovsdb-free.
(except _find_lost_vlan_port stuff, which is planned to be retired
by blueprint ofagent-merge-bridges)

Partially-Implements: blueprint ofagent-port-monitor
Change-Id: Ib4701f7c8ea0ee03229d207c0fbbf6f42a55aecb

commit_message:
Don't expose X-Auth-Token in cinder CLI

Cinder CLI exposes X-Auth-Token in debug mode. This patch replaces
X-Auth-Token's value with '{SHA1}<sha1oftoken>'. Some credentials
are exposed by keystoneclient as cinderclient uses keystoneclient
to authenticate, it will be fixed in bug:100414.

Change-Id: Id427bb08f24d146584053a6bc0b4751fee5a14a7
Partial-Bug: #1327019

Define Murano API URL explicitely

As our lab doesn't allow application_catalog publicURL to be set up
in keystone try to override this using 'url' parameter.

commit_message:
Add yum.rb provider for 5.0 and 5.0.1 with fixes

We found a critical bug in puppet's versioncmp function which deosn't
behave like RPM does, so we've implemented a new function as a fix.

Now we have to deliver this fix for both 5.0 and 5.0.1, because without
this fix the rollback to 5.0 and 5.0.1 will fails.

Related patch for fuel_upgrade script:

    https://review.openstack.org/#/c/111238/

Change-Id: Ic456a6f26fb2c33f4e8cddb3737ab3e0bca690e3
Blueprint: upgrade-to-5-1

commit_message:
fuel_upgrade: install few openstack releases

In Fuel 5.1 we will ship two openstack releases:

* 2014.1.1-5.1
* 2014.1.1-5.0.1

and we need to install them both. Since now it's possible to do.

Depends on a set of patches related to blueprint build-articats:

    https://review.openstack.org/#/q/project:stackforge/fuel-main+topic:bp/build-artifacts,n,z

Implements blueprint upgrade-to-5-1

Change-Id: I151534202de0aaac1bb7ae333a44b0b31b172b3b

commit_message:
Wizard config to openstack.yaml

 - removed wizard.json
 - all wizard config moved to base_release config
 - migration for 5.1 changed: already existing releases'
   "wizard_metadata" attribute is updated with
   proper data (i.e. without nsx info).

Change-Id: Ie6928b0e4b82882383fc74043a76f22400698b91
Closes-bug: 1348627

commit_message:
Convert Fn::Select to extended get_attr

Overcloud bootstrap_nodeid is now specified by parameter
BootStrapNodeResource with default value controller0.
This avoids the need to use Fn::Select on the mergy.py
built list of controllers to specify the first controller.

Change-Id: Id9cfeab50b90ceeeae51ea0e35997b7495b28cc4
Partial-Blueprint: tripleo-juno-remove-mergepy

What if a user has been revoked and all his tokens should be revoked? We cannot simply match on timestamps, regardless of the granularity of them, since all tokens that were issued before and after the user was revoked, should be revoked.'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-08-01 13:50:46.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

David - If something happens where all the tokens for a user should be revoked, then revoke_by_user would be called rather than revoke_by_expiration. -- http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/keystone/tree/keystone/contrib/revoke/core.py#n128

Then you'd get a revocation event that had a user_id and no expires_at, and that event would match any token with that user_id."}, {'account_id': 6534, 'date': '2014-08-01 14:31:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Revoke by expiration is conceptually unsound, since you can never guarantee that two events will never happen at the same time.

Making the time granularity coarser, to the nearest second rather than millisecond, makes this operation even worse.

No wonder Dolph said Yuk :-)'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-08-01 15:24:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

David / Dolph - if you have another suggestion for how to fix this I'd be happy to hear it. We can't use the token ID, since that would be anathema to the whole concept of revocation events, but revoking by expiration time seems to be a less-accurate version of revoking by token ID."}, {'account_id': 6534, 'date': '2014-08-01 19:42:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

If you want to revoke a token the natural thing to do is use the token ID, since this is unique to the token. It is how X.509 certs are revoked, for example.

I dont know the history of keystone revocation, so why do you say this is an anathema?'}, {'account_id': 6486, 'date': '2014-08-01 22:09:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

[{'created': '2014-07-31 22:48:23.000000000', 'message': "Fix revocation event handling with MySQL

When MySQL is used to store revocation events, events are returned
from the database with the timestamps truncated to the second. This
causes a revocation event for a token (which has the issued_at
timestamp to the microsecond) to not match the revocation event and
therefore the token is not considered to be revoked.

The fix is to have the revocation events and token timestamps both
always be truncated to the second. This will cause all tokens for a
user that are issued within a second to be revoked when any of those
tokens are revoked, which shouldn't be a problem.

Change-Id: Ibd82b4ce910206dfd504c396614ae2ebed025e9b
Closes-Bug: #1347961
"}]
commit_message:
Fix revocation event handling with MySQL

When MySQL is used to store revocation events, events are returned
from the database with the timestamps truncated to the second. This
causes a revocation event for a token (which has the issued_at
timestamp to the microsecond) to not match the revocation event and
therefore the token is not considered to be revoked.

The fix is to have the revocation events and token timestamps both
always be truncated to the second. This will cause all tokens for a
user that are issued within a second to be revoked when any of those
tokens are revoked, which shouldn't be a problem.

Change-Id: Ibd82b4ce910206dfd504c396614ae2ebed025e9b
Closes-Bug: #1347961

commit_message:
labs: make wait_for_file work with nounset

The wait_for_file function (used for debugging) can be called with or
without an argument. Called without an argument, it will trigger an
error if the nounset option is on (set -o nounset).

This problem is fixed by adding a default value (empty string) to the
function argument.

Change-Id: I5beebc9cbf8ab62678ab2a557b36b359f5c1f9e4

[{'created': '2014-07-31 11:25:11.000000000', 'message': 'labs: iniset_sudo: use privileges for reading, too

As noted in the commit message when the function was introduced,
iniset_sudo uses root privileges only for writing.

Turns out that this minimal set of root privilege use is not sufficient
for all client script needs. For instance, /etc/keystone permissions
deny access to anyone but the keystone user.

This patch allows iniset_sudo to work even if the regular user has no
permission to read the file.

Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I85b15703a59befa531cc99136a282bedc137cde1
'}]
commit_message:
labs: iniset_sudo: use privileges for reading, too

As noted in the commit message when the function was introduced,
iniset_sudo uses root privileges only for writing.

Turns out that this minimal set of root privilege use is not sufficient
for all client script needs. For instance, /etc/keystone permissions
deny access to anyone but the keystone user.

This patch allows iniset_sudo to work even if the regular user has no
permission to read the file.

Implements: blueprint openstack-training-labs
Change-Id: I85b15703a59befa531cc99136a282bedc137cde1

commit_message:
Add port check for murano deployment tests

- Refactor _try_port method
- Move _try_port method from savanna to NovaNetworkScenarioTest
- Change murano base class inheritance,
  now murano inherit from NovaNetworkScenarioTest
- Add ports check method which allow us to check needed ports
- Add "assignFloatingIp" in jsons
  for murano services(Telnet and Apache)

Change-Id: Icb2743e1e84b664542d7bdec4551a974c84a87e9
Implements-blueprint: additional-checks-for-murano-engine-tests

commit_message:
Check if volume is bootable when creating an instance

Cinder provides a bootable flags for volumes that's not being
checked when creating an instance.

If a user select a non-bootable volume, then the VM became unusable
since nothing will be booted at all.

This check is done only in case that a volume is selected as root
device for a VM.  Boot from snapshot will still work (even that the
volume will be marked as non-bootable by cinder, but will boot the
attached snapshot instead)
If the attribute bootable is not present, we keep the old behaviour
and allow the instance creation.
Conflicts:
	nova/compute/api.py

Change-Id: I8e028d40d6a11beeac4f043afccb17eb61f6ce62
Closes-Bug: #1321334
(cherry picked from commit 310231541661adaa30d92d357f7590c88dc905b3)

commit_message:
Add common units constants

We use numeric expression like 1024 * 1024 , or 1024 ** 2 in swift , we
can use common units constant to make code more readable. We have done
this in Oslo, Nova, Glance, and Cinder(approved,not merged). So let us
make it in Swift.

Implements blueprint: use-common-units

Change-Id: Iec55544bbb6ea124628d67d6e6a2308f007b64e0

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

commit_message:
Live migration is broken for NFS shared storage

One of the new checks, introduced in
I2755c59b4db736151000dae351fd776d3c15ca39
is missing a check against filebased shared storage,
leading to live migration being broken.

Closes-Bug: #1346385
Change-Id: I096ecd6eadc3b13ef918ca1e6c98acdd01556c0d

commit_message:
Allow to pass no unit to string_to_bytes

The regex used to validate the data input to string_to_bytes
wasn't matching those cases where non unit was specified to do
the conversion, although the function string_to_bytes was
ready for that.

Change-Id: Ia6d426eddc633964fcb1484211e232a38d172722

commit_message:
Allow to pass no unit to string_to_bytes

The reges used to validate the data input to string_to_bytes
wasn't matching those case where non unit was specified to do
the conversion, although the function string_to_bytes was
ready for that.

Change-Id: Ie07daf69abafdf93359b640a2558e55215d7fb15

commit_message:
Update strutils from oslo-incubator

As a preparation for a full update of the oslo-incubator
modules, those that require changes in ironic code, will
be done separately.

strutils.to_bytes function is now strutils.string_to_bytes

Change-Id: I9d956fef94ead56e630f6dedf72150134fe748a1

commit_message:
Move new manager code to a new module

This should help us differentiate between old (using native clients) and new
(using tempest clients) manager. The module will include only relevant code.
Once the migration to tempest clients is complete, we can easily deprecate the
old manager

Partially-implements bp:tempest-client-scenarios

Change-Id: I4218e6585b6ba9983b5529217d6c54d60bd000c8

commit_message:
Add docs for how to create an OAuth auth instance

Similar to the other authentication methods that were documented,
like password and token, this patch will add a brief description
on how to authenticate with the oauth1 plugin.

Change-Id: I1b7cceb116d337be71576139601f34ca17563a50

Comment from Tihomir sounds reasonable. Tatiana, could you try and address the comment?'}, {'account_id': 6914, 'date': '2014-07-30 10:33:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Tihomir, thank you for your suggestion. Each field is highlighted correctly, the same way it was done in the first patch set. However it appears that using 'clean_fieldname' breaks a whole bunch of almost unrelated unit tests. IMO it deserves at least a separate patch set. Moreover, it seems that almost everywhere in Horizon we use 'clean' with "private" fields like self._errors (see for example https://github.com/openstack/horizon/blob/master/openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/access_and_security/security_groups/forms.py#L360 etc). So my suggestion is to use the same way for fixing current bug and take the first patch set and to report a separate bug to replace all Horizon 'clean' with 'clean_fieldname'.

What do you think about it? Akihiro, Ana, your opinion?'}, {'account_id': 2455, 'date': '2014-07-30 11:49:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

Oh, in the example in my comment I've missed the return statements for each cleaning method. That's the reason the tests fail. Otherwise it works fine.

However, looking in the Django code, I've found that each field is cleaned through generic field cleaning functions and then looking for additional clean_fieldname method. In the current patch the 3 fields depend on self.cleaned_data["image_source"], which in theory might not be cleaned yet, hence missing from self.cleaned_data dictionary. So when one field depends on the value of other field - it seems better to use def clean() and self._errors instead. So the patchset 2 seems to be the right option.'}, {'account_id': 9647, 'date': '2014-07-30 15:27:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 6914, 'date': '2014-07-31 11:29:30.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Yes it seems that an additional dependency caused the tests fail. Adding return statements was the first thing I've done, but it hasn't fixed all tests using 'image_source'. Thank you for the clarification. commit_message:
Make source fields required for 'Create Volume' form

Raise an error message when 'Volume Source' field has been
changed to 'Image', 'Volume' or 'Snapshot' but no actual
image/volume/snapshot has been selected.

Closes-Bug: #1348760

Change-Id: I2d864c78ba2f5bce55f6fe77075ea6dd848f0f6a

commit_message:
Fix RBD store to use READ_CHUNKSIZE

Change 4e0c563b8f3a5ced8f65fcca83d341a97729a5d4 was incomplete and
missed a variable in the rbd store.

This patch fixes the issue by using store.READ_CHUNKSIZE instead of
store.chunk_size

Change-Id: I2dc5b1514d3e86ec129c1fc88de096d98a64f806
Closes-Bug: #1352509

subject: Decouple read chunk size from write chunk size

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-07-01 06:51:49.000000000', 'message': 'Make copy_from chunk size configurable

When using the copy_from option, readers and writers can have different
speeds to respectively read and write.
A reader can timeout if the connection has been opened for too long
without getting any heartbeat.
This is happening if the writer is slower than the reader. A reader
will have to wait for the writer to process all the bits sent before
getting the next chunk. If this time to process the bits is too long
the reader will timeout.
Consequently, the writer should be able to control the size of the
chunks that needs to be read in order to be able to write fast enough.

This patch addresses the issue by adding a COPY_FROM_CHUNKSIZE attribute
in the store which will be used by the reader (if defined).

Change-Id: I4e0c563b8f3a5ced8f65fcca83d341a97729a5d4
Closes-Bug: #1336168
'}, {'created': '2014-07-01 19:07:45.000000000', 'message': 'Make copy_from chunk size configurable

When using the copy_from option, readers and writers can have different
speeds to respectively read and write.
A reader timeout will happen if the writer is slow and the writer is
being asked to write a lot. This is currently happening when for using
the VMware store and copying from an HTTP server. The reader is reading
16MB which takes too long too upload to vCenter which is causing a
timeout from the HTTP server. The writer should be able to control the
size of the chunks being read when using copy_from.

This patch addresses the issue by adding a COPY_FROM_CHUNKSIZE attribute
in the store which will be used by the reader (if defined).

Change-Id: I4e0c563b8f3a5ced8f65fcca83d341a97729a5d4
Closes-Bug: #1336168
'}, {'created': '2014-07-01 19:09:54.000000000', 'message': 'Make copy_from chunk size configurable

commit_message:
Decouple read chunk size from write chunk size

When using the copy_from option, readers and writers can have different
speeds to respectively read and write.
A reader timeout will happen if the writer is slow and the writer is
being asked to write a lot. This is currently happening when using
the VMware store and copying from an HTTP server. The reader is reading
16MB which takes too long to upload to vCenter which is causing a
timeout from the HTTP server. The writer should be able to control the
size of the chunks being read when using copy_from: this way the writer
will write fast enough to not make the reader timeout.

This patch addresses the issue by introducing the notion of read chunk
size and write chunk size. Each store can have its own value for read
and write. The write chunk size of the destination store will be used
as the read chunk size of the source store in case of an image-create
where the copy_from option is specified.

Closes-Bug: #1336168

Signed-off-by: Arnaud Legendre <alegendre@vmware.com>
Signed-off-by: Zhi Yan Liu <zhiyanl@cn.ibm.com>

Change-Id: I4e0c563b8f3a5ced8f65fcca83d341a97729a5d4

commit_message:
Handle NetworkAmbiguous error when booting a new instance with v3 api

Catch exception.NetworkAmbiguous error and map it to exc.HttpConflict when
using v3 api to create a new instance.

Change-Id: I18b6b9f0d8612a3757f6489dada41b5cd8eca758
Closes-Bug: 1350800

commit_message:
Do not assume order of network_uuid's

This fixes the neutron.tests.unit.test_linux_dhcp.TestDnsmasq
.test_existing_dhcp_networks unit test that breaks with a
randomized PYTHONHASHSEED (see the bug report).

The test assumed that the network_uuid's list was sorted, so sort
the result before comparing.

Note: There are several other unrelated unit tests that also break with a
randomized PYTHONHASHSEED, but they are not addressed here. They will be
addressed in separate patches.

Partial-bug: #1348818
Change-Id: Ia6f742e1fae0687164b841beebb4efcf31ff2625

commit_message:
Rewrite ironic policy to use the new changes of common policy

The oslo has rewritten the common policy for a long time, using a
Enforer class to replace the old check function. In order to sync the
common policy to ironic, we have to also changed the ironic policy.
Sync policy and relate module from Oslo.
   Some related change-id:Ife909bdf3277ef33c2fb1eae16ae261fa6374c63
                change-id:Ife84189be4b86a3ee90da4539ff2dbed125be23d

Change-Id: I90c692cdde4741d8c547febb3eee5c24ea30ba8c

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-05-07 16:06:28.000000000', 'message': "Make sure that gateway is in CIDR range by default

Git commit c3706fa2 introduced the force_gateway_on_subnet
option that verified that the defined gateway is in the CIDR
range of a newly created or updated subnet. However, the default
value was False for backwards compatability reasons. I believe
the option should be deleted and the gateway should always
be in the requested CIDR. Another option would be to turn it
on by default, but considering Neutron has so many config options
(That make the life of deployers much harder), I think this
is the perfect example of an option that can simply be removed.

ip route add default [...] requires that the gateway address
be reachable. That is, to belong to one of the CIDRs on one of the
devices. So, a gateway could belong to a CIDR on another subnet
that is already present on the machine on another device.
I don't see how this could be useful so I vote to drop the
config option instead of changing the default.

Change-Id: I04fd1caec6da5dceee3f736b3f91f2468150ba2a
Closes-Bug: #1304181

will change to True and the option will be marked as deprecated.

For IPv6, the gateway must be in the CIDR only if the gateway

commit_message:
Make sure that gateway is in CIDR range by default

Git commit c3706fa2 introduced the force_gateway_on_subnet
option that verified that the defined gateway is in the CIDR
range of a newly created or updated subnet. However, the default
value was False for backwards compatability reasons. The default
will change to True and the option will be marked as deprecated.

For IPv6, the gateway must be in the CIDR only if the gateway
is not a link local address.

DocImpact
Change-Id: I04fd1caec6da5dceee3f736b3f91f2468150ba2a
Closes-Bug: #1304181

Working on a alternative way for logging errors in both cases.'}, {'account_id': 4601, 'date': '2014-08-01 14:00:45.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

After investigating the reschedule flow, I found out there is no sane way to have the same behavior, that is, log errors in conductor log for both cases (re-rescheduling disabled and enabled).

nova.compute.manager._reschedule is the method that calls the reschedule method and it skips the reschedule when there is no retry information in the filter_properties...

Maybe, when we completely move cold migration and build instance to conductor, we can have a consistent behavior for those errors logging. Or we can even move reschedule code to conductor before moving other things.

At this point, I'm going to abandon the change... unless someone has any thought how we could handle it.

Let me know if I'm missing anything."}, {'account_id': 4601, 'date': '2014-08-01 14:02:05.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Log errors in populate_retry even when max_attempt == 1

We should be logging errros even though retry is disabled.

Change-Id: I24444a547d2f1b42a0bc368d3d11fb3ecccab451
Closes-Bug: #1343858

commit_message:
Enable some volumes v2 tests by sharing codes part2

1. Rename volumes v1 client to a base client, then create
   v1 and v2 clients inheriting base client.
2. create volumes v2 tests using the existent test class.
3. create a new test class for v1, which inherits v2.

This patch includes the following volumes tests:
- test_availability_zone.py
- test_extensions.py

Partially implements: blueprint cinder-v2-api-tests

Change-Id: Ie21ebc184710e9abe894cdc20ed7a39aacc94ded

Hi Julien,

As it happens, Nejc & I discussed the feasibility of applying this approach to the partitioned alarm evaluator also, and it seems at first sight that this would be a simpler and more elegant solution than the approach currently used.

Specifically, the hashing pattern applied to alarm UUIDs would avoid the need for alarm assignment and allocation RPC calls from the master to the slaves.

Also we would no longer need the selective re-balancing logic in the partition coordinator, that kicks in when a certain threshold of alarm deletion is detected since the last re-balancing.

Cheers,
Eoghan'}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2014-08-04 12:38:07.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Chris, Gordon, Julien and Eoghan, thanks for the review and the feedback.

I hope most of the feedback is addressed in the latest patch, where I have added:

* a section clarifying what happens when a member joins/leaves a group

* a section proposing a reusable implementation of resource partitioning for use in other parts of Ceilometer (namely, alarm evaluation)

* further clarification of why the alternative approach with locking is worse than the proposed one.

If I forgot to address any of your feedback, please let me know. :-)

Cheers,

  I think this could have been merged after the presentation if it was chosen to be the better approach. I don't see the rush to get this in especially since nobody really had a chance to review it ..."}, {'account_id': 8052, 'date': '2014-08-04 17:02:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

I agree. I think the merge was largely accidental (a side-effect of 2 of the core developers +1 ing the patch). It wasn't a rush to get it merged, it was always my intention to consider your approach as well."}, {'account_id': 2284, 'date': '2014-08-05 07:29:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5:

@fabiog: fair point, my expectation was more that this review would accumulate multiple +2s before potentially landing only after the other spec was also fully compared and contrasted to this approach. I apologize, I should have been more explicit about that intention.

However, you shouldn't take this patch landing as a implicit -1 on your approach, as we'll consider your spec individually on its merits also (in the meeting scheduled for later on today).

Cheers,
Eoghan"}]

commit_message:
Sync oslo imageutils, strutils to Ironic

Changes in imageutils:
===============================
9e88af1 fixed typos found by RETF rules
b455fac Enable decimal value input in imageutils.QemuImgInfo
bec3a5e Implements SI/IEC unit system conversion to bytes
8b2b0b7 Use hacking import_exceptions for gettextutils._
aad179d Fixing misspelled encryption key in QemuImgInfo
12bcdb7 Remove vim header
2bd46eb Refactors byte size extraction logic
0356685 Adds common image utils

Changes in strutils:
====================
cb5a804 Move `mask_password` to strutils
8a0f567 Remove str() from LOG.* and exceptions
fd18c28 Fix safe_encode(): return bytes on Python 3
302c7c8 strutils: Allow safe_{encode,decode} to take bytes as input
bec3a5e Implements SI/IEC unit system conversion to bytes
e53fe85 strutils bool_from_string, allow specified default
8b2b0b7 Use hacking import_exceptions for gettextutils._
84d461e Fix a bug in safe_encode where it returns a bytes object in py3
12bcdb7 Remove vim header

Change-Id: If0d16d70c004344511b9851c8a533759f0d2bb52

commit_message:
Fixing wording in the content for Key management

The sentence that describes the provider liablity aspect
of it was not worded properly and this bug corrects
the sentence wording

There was a typo in the bug id and an additional number
got into the Bug number. Fixed it.

Changed the sentence wording as recommended.

Modified the sentence as per recommended grammar rules

Did the git rebase and committing the change

Closes-Bug: #1342296

commit_message:
WIP: Add a RESTful api server for Tempest

This is very rough implementation for Tempest RESTful API server for
Tempest.

TODO
    * Clean up the shell script of list_tempest.sh
    * Clean up the output format
    * Add input validations
    * Persistent test-id
    * Add a function of generating tempest.conf
    * Fix the paths of shell scripts
    * Add unit tests
    * More documentation
    * Fix async command execution

Implements blueprint add-tempest-server

Change-Id: Ib3e9a026475cf3be35eb13dc916074b284b36e13

Nice feature, I feel we need to consider API design(request/response body, method, url) more.'}, {'account_id': 5196, 'date': '2014-07-09 14:08:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

(4 comments)

So as much fun as I think this would be to work on. (which really is a lot, and if we move forward with this I'd definitely be on the list of contributors) I think the one section you're missing which is critical here is the alternatives. My primary concern with this is whether we actually need it or not. Which really is a question of what are we looking to solve with this effort.

During the summit session we discussed whether just using Jenkins could accomplish all of the goals of this spec. I'm not really sure of the answer, but I'm inclined to say yes. So before I'm comfortable giving this the +A I think we need to have a very detailed alternatives section. We also have to flush out a bit more on the why and what we're trying to solve with this spec. 

For example, is it just that the python testing workflow is too dense and difficult to use like you mentioned in the problem description. If so I'd say we could just solve that with a tempest binary that runs the tests.

I think at this point the technical details are secondary to these more abstract questions. (of course, I'm not sure a spec review is the best place to handle this, it might require more f2f conversation) Once we get these things sorted out then we can move forward."}, {'account_id': 5689, 'date': '2014-08-05 06:57:15.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

We need to find clear reason to move forward this.'}]

commit_message:
Add tempest server/client/GUI spec

This commit adds a tempest server/client/GUI spec. As we discussed at
Atlanta Design summit, we should have the features of server/client/GUI
of Tempest. And this spec describes very high level design of the
features. So details should be described in other specs.

Partially implements blueprint add-tempest-server-client-gui

Change-Id: I5f0b12a3a272caa5c0d28dde84a7681f792509be

commit_message:
Filter users by email

It has been discussed before that the email shouldn't be added as an
attribute for the user model, but now with the adding of filtering with
attributes that are available in the `extra` section of the model. It is
possible to filter users by email by adding that attribute to the
filterprotected decorator.

Given the nature of this attribute, it is a common use case that
applications will try to filter users by it. Thus, the adding of this to
the available filters has value.

Change-Id: I0fa87eb0ade2491c89fbbf6b233db25c98ec0917
Closes-Bug: #1211582

commit_message:
Add support for user_id based authentication with Neutron

Keystone v3 supports non-unique project/user names, so until
the Neutron client provides support for the V3 API and domain
based authentication Nova should allow user ID for admin
authentication.

Change-Id: Idad27ff4206d6ba0bb9aedbbff5172c3144ad3c6
DocImpact: Adds new flag, neutron.admin_user_id

commit_message:
Handle MacAddressInUseClient exception from Neutron when creating port

This adds exception handling for the new MacAddressInUseClient exception
from python-neutronclient-2.3.6 when trying to create a port with a
specific MAC address.

The PortInUse exception is used so that the build will be rescheduled if
this error is encountered.

Also, the servers API already handles PortInUse and translates it to an
HTTPConflict response.

Closes-Bug: #1347778

Change-Id: I929b5f9d79bcb7e60e8b3482e5ee1ca2fababed1

commit_message:
Commit quota when deallocate floating ip

It seems that when you allocate a floating-ip in a tenant with nova-network,
its quota is never returned after calling 'nova floating-ip-delete'
even though 'nova floating-ip-list' shows it gone.
This behavior applies to each tenant individually. The gate tests are passing
because they all run with tenant isolation.

The root cause of the problem is cooperation between
commit 23a27e47 and cbbb9de5. db layer code return floatingip_ref
but object layer didn't. This patch fixed the problem by adding return
value from object layer.

Change-Id: Ide1a338b6c33676311028e8738150e146324a8ee
Closes-Bug: #1347156

Delete Stacks button doesn't work

Clicking on causes a frozen grey overlay.
It should have the class 'btn-danger' and remove the 'ajax-modal' class.

(1 comment)

I strongly disagree with the link between CGs and disaster recover / remote replication. Replicaiton can benefit from a grouping concept, but those groups will have little or nothing in common with CGs.

CGs are an important concept with a (reasonably) well understood use case. CGs are a way for users/tenants to tell the system which resources need to be in sync with eachother for the purpose of snapshots. In this case, CGs provide a way for the user to give cinder additional information that it wouldn't otherwise have (i.e. volume x and volume y are related to eachother at the application layer).

Replication groups serve no purpose other than to work around the limitation that certain backends (i.e. NetApp, GlusterFS) have where replication is performed at the container level rather than at the volume level, which means that it's not possible to break a replication relationship on one volume without affecting others. In this case, the groups provide a way for backends to cinder where the replication container boundaries are, so administrators can cope with the fact that management of replication relationship is somewhat coarse-grained.

I would be happy with this proposal is we either
* Dropped any mention of CGs applying to DR/replication or
* Do the hard work of figuring out how groups works w.r.t. DR/replication and write that down"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-06-28 11:53:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7:

commit_message:
Add Consistency Groups Support in Cinder

This proposal is to add Consistency Groups support in Cinder.
It will be implemented for snapshots in phase 1.

blueprint: consistency-groups
Change-Id: I777338610662c89dbb0a7501173f0dcd6bbe5386

commit_message:
Remove instance_info_cache_delete() from conductor

This was not used in v2.0 of the RPC API, so we can remove it
outright without deprecating it in conductor manager.

Related to blueprint compute-manager-objects-juno

[{'created': '2014-07-24 14:07:53.000000000', 'message': 'Fix Over-writing virt driver stats field

Some virt drivers return a stats field in the result when
queried for available resources. This gets over-written by
the resource tracker. This fix checks to see if there is
a stats field already present and if so does not recreated
it.

Change-Id: I60fc400379970947bfd089c3270523a789153c96
Closes-bug: #1347795
'}]
commit_message:
Fix Over-writing virt driver stats field

Some virt drivers return a stats field in the result when
queried for available resources. This gets over-written by
the resource tracker. This fix checks to see if there is
a stats field already present and if so does not recreated
it.

Change-Id: I60fc400379970947bfd089c3270523a789153c96
Closes-bug: #1347795

commit_message:
Fix tempest compatibility

Manila's cli tempest test 'test_manila_fake_action', located in
contrib/tempest/tempest/cli/simple_read_only/test_manila.py
fails due to incompatibility affected by Tempest commit:
https://github.com/openstack/tempest/commit/aeb5274fd4f4c3658c14d44af7d02ccd907501e0

this change fixes mentioned test to be compatible with current Tempest
master branch state.

commit_message:
Handle service creation race by service workers

This handle a race where a sibling has already created the service
record in the database.  This fix is similar to that of commit
f6c341b4.

Change-Id: I7975fc632eee34390c5d7dc275b52363ad45475e
Closes-bug: 1326901
(cherry picked from commit 37247aba813fbc408901a2f1b1ad88e2acb796a1)

commit_message:
Fix listener for update.start notifications

When listening for update.start, ceilometer-notification-agent
will raise a KeyError exception. This is because, the "id" in notification
message is in message['payload'] not the message['payload'][resource].

Change-Id: I6dd56fbf31c29e26670068004f6fc935b91266f0
Closes-Bug: #1325172

commit_message:
Fixed text on create cluster dialog

* In CreateCluster the action from cluster templates was used
* In jobs SelectHadoopPluginAction the template from cluster templates
  was used
* SelectPlugin and SelectPluginAction in jobs were never used.

Change-Id: I3affd88b49b36ec13e1a77f720bdad1da076fd7b
Closes-Bug:  bug #1336266
Co-Authored-By: Andrew Lazarev <alazarev@mirantis.com>

This patch clarifies two elements:

1. According to Shibboleth's documentation the ShibRequireAll command
is not supported on Apache 2.4+, details can be found at
https://wiki.shibboleth.net/confluence/display/SHIB2/NativeSPApacheConfig

2. Some configurations of Apache + Shibboleth SP will always set the

"}]
commit_message:
Improve instructions about federation

This patch clarifies two elements:

1. According to Shibboleth's documentation the ShibRequireAll command
is not supported on Apache 2.4+, details can be found at
https://wiki.shibboleth.net/confluence/display/SHIB2/NativeSPApacheConfig

2. Some configurations of Apache + Shibboleth SP will always set the
REMOTE_USER env variable, even if it is an empty value; this can
lead to unexplained authentication errors that can be avoided if the
external auth method is disabled.

Change-Id: Iaf4e57e7e3d79a2e87e805bbe8340861ee9c3db3

commit_message:
Moved core int-test groups from trove-int to trove

Cleaned up int-test dependencies so that the core int-test groups
are now registered entirely from trove python module. This enables
adding new int-tests for features in trove without creating a cross
repository dependency on trove-integration.

Change-Id: I8ed85d5cb488c402c86b72c4f3cc23389098aa83
Partial-bug: 1343584

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC

commit_message:
Fixed cannot delete router port because of permission denied

Removed the condition check in allowed function that is defined in the RemoveInterface class
which makes no sense because it is set in the delete function that runs after allowed function.

Closes-Bug: #1234447
Change-Id: I6cf8280d9355dcd3310b08932f62022852fac8ee

commit_message:
Update wording to make more sense for metadata changes.

The wording is updated to say 'flavor' instead of 'instance'
in a lot of places where 'flavor type' makes more sense to
see when reading through the page. The wording 'instance type'
is not always clear, and since the changes are for flavor
metadata, this made more sense.

(Fixed a couple 'extra specs' to be 'extra_specs' like the
rest of the places it is.)

Change-Id: I702481e6b67536852efc3a0747b29be811cf792f

commit_message:
Clean up default tox environment list

Reorder the list to place python 3.3 first to avoid the issue with
python 2.6/7 choosing a dbm format not available in 3.3.

Remove python 3.2 from the default list so that running tox without any
arguments runs a useful set of tests.

Change-Id: I181f73871df16b44de6426f7cddc40956e338c72

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-04 17:17:11.000000000', 'message': 'Make spawn_n() stub properly ignore errors in the child thread work

When we call spawn_n() normally, we fork off a thread that can run or
die on its own, without affecting the parent. In unit tests, we stub
this out to be a synchronous call, but we allow any exceptions that
occur in that work to bubble up to the caller. This is not normal
behavior and thus we should discard any such exceptions in order to
mimic actual behavior of a child thread.

Change-Id: I35ab21e9525aa76cced797436daa0b99a4fa99f2
Related-bug: #1349147
'}]
commit_message:
Make spawn_n() stub properly ignore errors in the child thread work

When we call spawn_n() normally, we fork off a thread that can run or
die on its own, without affecting the parent. In unit tests, we stub
this out to be a synchronous call, but we allow any exceptions that
occur in that work to bubble up to the caller. This is not normal
behavior and thus we should discard any such exceptions in order to
mimic actual behavior of a child thread.

Change-Id: I35ab21e9525aa76cced797436daa0b99a4fa99f2
Related-bug: #1349147

commit_message:
Fixed a ValueError on provisioning cluster

If the machine is slow, the remote command may output an empty string.
Converting an empty string to an integer results a ValueError, which
caused a failure. This patch attempted to fix the error by adding a
check for the outputted string before converting to integer.

Closes-Bug: 1351624
Change-Id: I38aadaa8c6b3ae9c7f93f90d5144ac8de7aa54d4

commit_message:
Fix revoking a scoped token from an unscoped token

When a scoped token that was created from an unscoped token was
revoked, the original token wound up being revoked. This is because
the scope wasn't included in the revocation event. By including the
scope in the revocation event only the scoped token is revoked.

Change-Id: I5652663ab7e1176d3b1efc5d218a8a020498067e
Closes-Bug: #1347318

commit_message:
EndpointNotFound deleting volume backend instance

When there is some error in volume creating on booting from volume,
we may get the EndpointNotFound exception when deleting the error instance.
Then we can never delete the instance successfully. The exception should
be ignored.

Change-Id: Ia92b648eb18c70996747d361e227de771f33ee9c
Closes-bug: 1346866

Issue was introduced by https://review.openstack.org/#/c/76354/
In case of recovarable exceptions message is None and exc_value
need to be used. But after encoding.force_unicode(message) message
becomes u'None' and all checks on "if message" pass. This result
in popup screen with 'None' text instead of problem description.

commit_message:
Fixed error message for recoverable exceptions

Issue was introduced by https://review.openstack.org/#/c/76354/
In case of recovarable exceptions message is None and exc_value
need to be used. But after encoding.force_unicode(message) message
becomes u'None' and all checks on "if message" pass. This result
in popup screen with 'None' text instead of problem description.

Change-Id: I7bc2dd02f97ba2bb10a7fadd2c1b86b011eb5967
Closes-Bug: #1350110

commit_message:
Designate API tests for Tempest Framework

Creates a new folder 'tempest' under 'designate/contrib' as a
placeholder for Designate API tests.
This submission implements CRUD operations on 'domains', 'records'
and 'servers' of Designate Api.
Adds related JSON supporting methods in client files
'domains_client.py', 'records_client.py', and 'server_client.py'
Also implemented schema validation for all the operations under
'domains.py', 'parameter_types.py', 'records.py', 'servers.py' files.
Modified 'tempest.conf.sample', 'config.py' , and 'clients.py' to
add parameters for enabling designate service.

Change-Id: I5fcac06200ce534a9cddf1e7ed9393ae5124a681

commit_message:
ofagent: Desupport ancillary bridges

Remove code to report port status for ancillary bridges because
it relies on ovsdb.  While we could adapt the code to use OFP in
a similar way we did for the integration bridge, it doesn't worth
the effort because the almost same functionality can be achieved
using provider network.  Update README to suggest the use of
provider network.

Partially-Implements: blueprint ofagent-port-monitor
Change-Id: Ia1329e36755b3e9a479a115dbd08aa3f4d6b55df

commit_message:
Relabel filesystem if SELinux is available

Relabel the filesystem during image builds if SELinux is available
on the build machine. Otherwise touch /.autorelabel to schedule a
relabel the first time the image boots.

We relabel when possible because it decreases first boot time.

Change-Id: If04459bfa047d527cb30ad074387ebdbb12cab9a
Partial-Bug: 1347845

commit_message:
Fixes migrate_volume_completion

The following issues are addressed:

The source volume is never deleted when a migration is done because
status_update was assumed to always be a dict.

Unattached volumes are set to in-use when retyped.

In-use migrated volumes are left in status attaching.

Change-Id: Ib5034679a5f469ba53e6280a47e8c94d633cf911
Partial-Bug: 1316079

commit_message:
Add Fujitsu ETERNUS DX support

Support protocols
-Fibre Channel
-iSCSI

Support functions
-create/delete volume
-create/delete snapshot
-attach/detach volume
-list snapshots
-create volume from snapshot
-create volume from image
-create volume from volume
-create image from volume
-extend volume
-volume migration(host assisted)

modify code style to conform to pep8
modify snapshot test script
modify _find_lun find for lun using volume['ElementName'] and volume['DeviceID']
Change-Id: Ib5a4c5d61ef74c52138c21ce8fb69548f0eb6c29
Implements: blueprint fujitsu-dx-volume-driver

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

    IRC: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/IRC

commit_message:
Add Fujitsu ETERNUS DX support

Support protocols
-Fibre Channel
-iSCSI

Support functions
-create/delete volume
-create/delete snapshot
-attach/detach volume
-list snapshots
-create volume from snapshot
-create volume from image
-create volume from volume
-create image from volume
-extend volume
-volume migration(host assisted)

modify code style to conform to pep8 and pylint
modify snapshot test script
modify _find_lun find for lun using volume['ElementName'] and volume['DeviceID']

Change-Id: I5c646ff362b7bc03d5a276888fc066ed39638264
Implements: blueprint fujitsu-dx-volume-driver

[{'created': '2014-08-04 21:03:33.000000000', 'message': 'Use admin credentials only for glance upload

Sourcing the admin credentials before the image building causes an issue
where the DISTRO flag is being reset. It is sufficient to source the
admin credentials immediately before the glance upload.

Change-Id: I30870a236e155462cc5c4e72ffe5c65e4c190a09
'}]
commit_message:
Use admin credentials only for glance upload

Sourcing the admin credentials before the image building causes an issue
where the DISTRO flag is being reset. It is sufficient to source the
admin credentials immediately before the glance upload.

Change-Id: I30870a236e155462cc5c4e72ffe5c65e4c190a09

commit_message:
Don't override tox envdir for pep8 and cover jobs

infra's run-pep8 and run-coverage jobs assume the envdir for pep8 and
cover jobs are not overwritten, so it can call out to .tox/pep8/bin/pip
and .tox/coverage/bin/pip respectively.

This bug is causing keystone pep8 and coverage jobs to occasionally fail
in the gate.

If the motivation behind overriding the envdir jobs to use venv, one can
use devpi and/or wheels to speed up the process of building a venv.

Change-Id: I32cd46152caa73e1308fdd216ba016c80a5a9b4f
Closes-Bug: #1352134

commit_message:
Introduce iSCSI driver for Pure Storage FlashArray

This patch introduces an iSCSI driver for Pure Storage FlashArray to Cinder.
It impliments all required features.

Certification test results:
    https://bugs.launchpad.net/cinder/+bug/1347109

Change-Id: I25f465b4abfc19d9b2717ec095c65201e76beab9
Impliements: blueprint pure-iscsi-volume-driver

commit_message:
Add a test for revoking a scoped token from an unscoped

There was no test that showed that when a scoped token created from
an unscoped token is revoked that the unscoped token also winds up
being revoked.

Change-Id: I2c1574573488bb60a059c5d7f8747d6a1977aab7
Partial-Bug: #1347318

commit_message:
Set version of master tree to 0.9.0

This ensures that the sdist tarballs are actually getting
a version number higher than the released version 0.8.x,
which is need to correctly being able to identify the
code base they have been created from.

Change-Id: I77e9c7346e109f861c99bc95af7a9bd17436c338

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-04 03:58:26.000000000', 'message': "Remove debug CADF payload for every authN request

Currently, we are logging the payload every time a user logs in,
(twice actually, pending + success/failure.
This seems unnecessary since no other notifications log the debug
message, and the notification is sent anyway. The user may as well
set the notification_driver value to 'log' if he wants to actually
log the notification messages.

Closes-Bug: #1352115
Change-Id: I3bdf726ee2b32c434497b8c9372e2ab4cc8853cf
"}, {'created': '2014-08-04 05:08:22.000000000', 'message': "Remove debug CADF payload for every authN request

Since we already provide a generic mechanism for logging notifications
(setting the notification_driver value to 'log'), having an additional
debug log just for this case seems unnecessary.

Closes-Bug: #1352115
Change-Id: I3bdf726ee2b32c434497b8c9372e2ab4cc8853cf
"}]
commit_message:
Remove debug CADF payload for every authN request

Since we already provide a generic mechanism for logging notifications
(setting the notification_driver value to 'log'), having an additional
debug log just for this case seems unnecessary.

Closes-Bug: #1352115
Change-Id: I3bdf726ee2b32c434497b8c9372e2ab4cc8853cf

commit_message:
Fixing wording in the content for Key management

The sentence that describes the provider liablity aspect
of it was not worded properly and this bug corrects
the sentence wording

There was a typo in the bug id and an additional number
got into the Bug number. Fixed it.

Changed the sentence wording as recommended.

Modified the sentence as per recommended grammar rules

Did the git rebase and committing the change

Closes-Bug: #1342296

Change-Id: I2b41562a30e3dfc8588b2af5040d3992727f2b8f

commit_message:
Only get image location attributes if including locations

Commit 155eeabbfafd4f48b47fea5b403f61a6e5c28426 added 'direct_url' and
'locations' to the list of attributes to get from an image which makes a
call back to glance if the attributes aren't on the image, and can
result in a 404 if they aren't available, which would be in the glance
v1 API case.

This change simply passes the new include_locations parameter down to
_extract_attributes so we can do the proper filtering.

Change-Id: I903fa5c781fed52183b340dc3d9bc4b6598b21ce
Partial-Bug: #1351333

commit_message:
Refactor UpdateReplace exception

Use six.text_type to format error message, so that we can avoid
possible failure in unittest when switching to oslo.i18n.

Change-Id: I6979a3298ff5c3dac734bd7ad5534853bab1a7d8

commit_message:
Verify Help button redirects to the right URL

When choosing "Help", in the top bar user drop-down menu,
the browser should redirect to http://docs.openstack.org/
Different distributions might customize the redirection URL,
but the above should be the default.

I added test_dashboard_help_redirection.py, go_to_help_page
method in basepage and the help_url value to horizon.conf
(also forced a change in config.py)

Partially implements blueprint: selenium-integration-testing
Closes-Bug #1350408

Change-Id: I64e661690ee9c26eb9d69092024465ab1c15b8a1

commit_message:
Bump oslo.rootwrap to 1.3.0.0a1 for Cinder

Cinder already requires oslo.rootwrap 1.3.0 filters so we need to
bump requirements accordingly.

This will fix a variety of rootwrap warnings that can occur when using
the new cgroups features.

Change-Id: Ia72444d054a35c3dbb34c24dbefe8f05cdebbd33
Closes-bug: #1340877

commit_message:
Remove duplicate index from block_device_mapping table

Migration 186 (doesn't exist anymore) deleted the column virtual_name
from the the block_device_mapping table. This ended up modifying an
index (block_device_mapping_instance_uuid_virtual_name_device_name_idx)
to be identical to (block_device_mapping_instance_uuid_device_name_idx)

Closes-Bug: 1265839
Change-Id: Ib293220eb764e9810212d121ce7889e6aefc266e

commit_message:
Fix and Gate on E265

pep8 E265 makes sure block comment start with '# '. Fix and gate on this
new rule as it helps improve comment readability.

In the few cases where the comment was just commented out code, remove
the comment.

Change-Id: Iea1c445df8ddc2b6c17a4ab697ad756eef2f91fa

commit_message:
Hierarchical Projects

This patch adds the basic features to implement the
hierarchical projects concept. Some of the changes are:
- Add parent_project_id attribute to Project manager (and
  database column)
- list_project_parents() method
- list_project_children() method
- is_leaf_project() method
- Changes at create_project(), update_project() and
  delete_project()
- Restrict project tree depth on keystone.conf
- Unit tests

Co-Authored-By: Raildo Mascena <raildo@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>
Co-Authored-By: Telles Mota Vidal Nobrega <tellesmvn@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>
Co-Authored-By: Andre Aranha <afaranha@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>
Co-Authored-By: Samuel de Medeiros Queiroz <samuel@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>
Co-Authored-By: Thiago Paiva Brito <thiagop@lsd.ufcg.edu.br>

Implements: blueprint hierarchical-multitenancy
Change-Id: I8d579d3fb413cdacc3d7bcbd3ac3ed335b2ca05e

commit_message:
WIP Make target to port to HOT

This is the Makefile and sed generator required to port the
tripleo templates to HOT as per
Ib3cbb83f6ae94adb7b793ab1b662bd5c55cbb5b3.

DO NOT MERGE, this change is just to expose the conversion process
for reviews.

Change-Id: Ib9f7c5348de114a935313450606a423eab188f6d
Partial-Blueprint: tripleo-juno-remove-mergepy

commit_message:
Prevent extra API call when hostname not available

Due to recent Trove "list" API call change, hostname/IP is now returned.
So if hostname is not present in object, it is not available at all and
an additional API call should be prevented.

Change-Id: I77e80322e9b12b936064845f85f7ec15e1475bfb
Closes-Bug: #1341696

commit_message:
Convert network/api.py get calls to use Network object

This makes the network api module use the Network objects for
get() and get_all() operations. There were no tests for these methods,
so this patch adds them in the process.

Related to blueprint compute-manager-objects-juno

Change-Id: Iea1104a111e50a796077cdf0ed5b0f4e75bfcbcb

[{'created': '2014-08-04 12:56:01.000000000', 'message': "Add a tox test environment for random hashseed testing

The newer versions of tox by default enable a random PYTHONHASHSEED. However,
this breaks many Neutron unit tests, so PYTHONHASHSEED=0 is currently hard-

commit_message:
Add a tox test environment for random hashseed testing

The newer versions of tox by default enable a random PYTHONHASHSEED. However,
this breaks many Neutron unit tests, so PYTHONHASHSEED=0 is currently hard-
coded for Neutron's unit test environments.

We want to clean up the unit test cases that break with a random hashseed
(there are many). To be able to find the broken tests and then verify them,
we need to have an easy way of enabling random hashseed testing.

Partial-bug: #1348818

Change-Id: I51f05cdfa9f8728baabaf315b71e5defb26426b1

commit_message:
Add policy on how patches and reviews go hand in hand

There is currently a misconception about how a patch gets merged:
Author proposes a patch, review team reviews it. Us, and Them. Instead
it should be a 'We.'
If the review bandwidth doesn't grow at the same rate as the patch
proposal rate then we end up with a massive backlog where people are
pinging cores for reviews.

Record a recommended policy of asking patch authors to offset the review
resources spent on their patch by reviewing other patches.

Change-Id: I50653f8ea58240fa664519f544ce16b2adf39006

commit_message:
Do not override venvs

OpenStack infra jobs assume the virtual environments are setup in
a specific way. Do not override the virtual environments in any
tox target.

Change-Id: I7fa964207be08a99ef7b3573e2b8bb49b7b96f55
related-bug: #1352134

commit_message:
Allow HEAD for POST tempurls

HEAD requests are already allowed for GET and PUT tempurls; this
commit adds that for POST tempurls. Since POST replaces all the
object's metadata, it's quite useful to be able to HEAD the object in
order to fetch the old metadata and do a client-side merge of the new
metadata (like with normal, token-authenticated POST requests).

Change-Id: I603c7822cd27f0e304fd27024f83f95114eb0aef

commit_message:
Add libssl-dev for Ubuntu

Rebuilding pyOpenSSL requires the SSL development libraries. This is
present in files/rpms/general, but was missed in files/apts/general.

Change-Id: Ie3c688e2d74485eb7f981363633bbddab5da7046

First of all: handy tip about clicking the test results to be able to see it rendered. That's way easier. :)

Second: I think the bits about sending the terminal etag aren't quite right; we're not going to be sending over just the etag, but a whole serialized dictionary of extra metadata and possibly other goodies.

IIRC from the last meeting thingy, the request to the object server will look like this:

Content-Length: <N + B + TM + 4>
X-Trailing-Metadata-Boundary: <B random-looking bytes, probably 32 or so>
X-Trailing-Metadata-Length: <TM>

<obj data - fragment archive or whatever>
\r\n
<B random-looking bytes>
\r\n
<a serialized dictionary, TM bytes in length>

That lets us be very certain that we've gotten the whole thing and not a truncated read somehow (probably not due to network failures, but more likely from all the bugs we're gonna write). Also, we can send over arbitrary data instead of just an etag, so there's a good chance it'll serve us well in future."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-18 19:18:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: -Verified

commit_message:
Erasure Code Support for Swift

This is the first draft of the spec, lots of TODO and questions
to cover.  Not sure how it will render either, some pics included,
so will push it on up and see how it looks... also many rst
formatting errors to work through so for now please just focus
on content

Change-Id: Ic4e036317973c61fde1e524a3c7ccb255d9f4718

[{'created': '2014-06-19 03:32:22.000000000', 'message': "Revert 'V2 Pause: treat case when driver does not implement the operation'

Patch I7763f462dd8f61c29c79038d881dc015482a9b5c assume compute manager
can report a NotImplementedError to api layer so it can catch the exception
and report to end operator. Unfortuneately that's not true, according to
review comments in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/99325/
The compute api sends resetnetwork as an RPC cast to the compute manager,
so this exception will not propagate back up to the api.

So revert the original change to prevent further similar actions.

Change-Id: I7cbb8179b3eec8496b90ff5cf07397522d52c5de

commit_message:
Remove pause/unpause NotImplementedError API layer

There are 2 kinds of RPC call from API layer to compute layer,
one is cast and another is call. For cast, the RPC message will
be posted and the API service will not wait for the message to
be processed. So it won't be able to catch the exception raised
in compute layer, so catch and handle the exception is useless
and error leading. This patch removes code in API layer for
pause and unpause functions.

Change-Id: I7cbb8179b3eec8496b90ff5cf07397522d52c5de

commit_message:
Do not assume order of quotas dictionary elements

This fixes the quotas db unit test that breaks with a randomized PYTHONHASHSEED
(see the bug report).

The test assumed that the quotas dictionary from plugin.get_all_quotas() had
elements in a particular order. Found with PYTHONHASHSEED=1235130571.

The fix refactors the test case to handle an unsorted quotas dictionary. Also
choose some different quota limits to make it clearer what is being verified.

Partial-bug: #1348818

Note: There are several other unrelated unit tests that also break with a
randomized PYTHONHASHSEED, but they are not addressed here. They will be
addressed in separate patches.

Change-Id: I3892b51082629e6ebce175f64f501717741baa37

commit_message:
Fix revoking domain-scoped tokens

A token scoped to a domain wouldn't be revoked for a domain-wide
revocation event. This is because the code to convert a token to a
dict for revocation event processing didn't handle domain-scoped
tokens.

Partial-Bug: #1349597

Change-Id: Ib2c58f3fc8790dbe7f8b073d18d3fa9b0dff608d

[{'created': '2014-06-22 02:02:43.000000000', 'message': "Added Murano config checks

This patch enables check to make sure that murano-api.conf.sample
is always up to date. To make sure that your change keeps the sample
config in sync you can run:
$ tox -e pep8

It'll generate a config file from current source code and will
compare it with etc/murano/murano.sample.conf

getopt workaround for OS X users:
* install GNU getopt by using homebrew (brew install gnu-getopt) or
  macports (port install getopts);
* add it to the PATH before the actual getopt before running tox;
* if you'd like to make it default just add it to your bashrc/zshrc/etcrc,
  for example, for brew you should add:
  export PATH=$(brew --prefix gnu-getopt)/bin:$PATH

Side effects:
Turns out our code depends on posix_ipc through
openstack/common/lockutils.py. Added it to requirements.txt

Change-Id: I57b3660b8a15e17c88040d4b190b36364cd7c5bf
Closes-bug: #1291318

commit_message:
Added Murano config checks

This patch enables check to make sure that murano-api.conf.sample
is always up to date. To make sure that your change keeps the sample
config in sync you can run:
$ tox -e pep8

It'll generate a config file from current source code and will
compare it with etc/murano/murano.sample.conf

getopt workaround for OS X users:
* install GNU getopt by using homebrew (brew install gnu-getopt) or
  macports (port install getopts);
* add it to the PATH before the actual getopt before running tox;
* if you'd like to make it default just add it to your bashrc/zshrc/etcrc,
  for example, for brew you should add:
  export PATH=$(brew --prefix gnu-getopt)/bin:$PATH

Side effects:
Turns out our code depends on posix_ipc through
openstack/common/lockutils.py. Added it to requirements.txt

Change-Id: I57b3660b8a15e17c88040d4b190b36364cd7c5bf
Closes-bug: #1291318

commit_message:
Re-word the Building Blocks first paragraph

The first paragraph of the building block section of the compute admin
guide implies that an ephemeral instance will loose it's state on
shutdown of the instance.  Shutdown may imply deletion, but as there
is a shutdown state that does not remove the ephemeral volume, it
is more appropriate to talk about the deletion of the virtual
instance.  This change addresses that inconsistency.

Removed excess spaces
Removed Nova-Volume reference

Change-Id: If00ef49fecdf864f74efc7171850bbacd60dbcd0

commit_message:
Setup for syncing of glossary

These files are used by an infra script to sync files from
openstack-manuals to security-doc and operations-guide repositories.

The file projects-to-sync.txt contains a list of repositories to update
and sync-projects.sh handles the copying of files. This is a very simple
script to get the job done.

implements bp common-glossary-setup

Change-Id: I55be62393213a5ea2657face0f6f5f8bed1b982c

commit_message:
Log translation hint for nova.api

Currently, Log translation is motivated by oslo's move to prioritized
translation of strings, as documented at
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/LoggingStandards#Log_Translation

- add log translation hints for warning, error and info levels
- move from LOG.warning to LOG.warn
- remove use of % as a string formatter, use the log functionality
  instead

Change-Id: I128da6cbb2be1b5b51b4a79fb38b3bf8206431d9

commit_message:
Require mongodb >= 2.2 or fail misserably

The patch adds a minimum requirement for mongodb. This will provide a
useful error message to users when the installed mongodb version doesn't
match the minimum required one.

Change-Id: Iff8bb1645e7276529230da58c408552bebd8647a

commit_message:
Add share_server_id filter option to 'get_all' share API method

Added one more filter option - 'share_server_id' to 'get_all' method,
by default only admin can list shares with it.
Also made little refactor for this method and covered with unittests.
Added tempest tests to cover changes.

Partially-implements blueprint add-admin-api-list-shares-for-share-server

Change-Id: I54f5458d3bb365c7a6fd0c8c7dce664cc7d01fc2

commit_message:
Arch Design: Move introductory sections up

Move the introductory sections one level up, removing the separate
section for them. This reads much nicer in HTML now.
There's also no need to name the first paragraphs of a chapter
"Introduction", this is implied.

Change-Id: Ife4275807561dae2ca57dc71b7602240efa94663

commit_message:
Fix method for retrieving device address due to licence usage issue

Reasons:
 - Reimplement method for retrieving networking interface address
   due to licence usage issue.
 - Initially, code that was merged was found at
   http://goo.gl/E7Okx (stackoverflow)
   (all code that being posted there can be used under Apache 2.0).
 - after research was found that this code was initially posted at
   http://goo.gl/5U1Bfy (copyrights by ActiveState)

Changes:
 - Implementing networking utils by using netifaces;
 - replacing old(get_ip_address from operating_system module) method
   with new method from networking_utils.py;
 - fixing tests.
 - adding new dependency:
   - netifaces>=0.10.4

Change-Id: I0c299af3098c0cd4f295060ea62da57376fd4e7e
Closes-Bug: #1352246

commit_message:
Allow use of ceph backend for Cinder

Add an env var that will tell devstack-gate to configure devstack with
the ceph backend.  The value used comes from the example commit that
was forcibly enabling ceph for testing purposes here:

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/107472/7/stack.sh

Change-Id: I87bcaff25180abadbedb2400fa9476ccaf3b1e41

commit_message:
Add ceph to features.yaml

Add base ceph support to features.yaml.  By adding "ceph" to
ENABLED_SERVICES for devstack, ceph will be used to back both glance
and Nova.  Cinder support will be added in another change.

Change-Id: I77e609f2bf7e9fca1351f0d22dc90ba96efcd0a4

Lint-based cleanup of 2 scss files

resource_browser.scss and horizon_workflow.scss should be cleaned up
from a lint-like perspective.

commit_message:
Proper port for LBaaS members

This patch set makes loadbalancer select a port on pool subnet
for new members if possible.

Closes-Bug: #1288859

Change-Id: I0809908ec5d15a448691dccf526b66308cf929d4

commit_message:
Remove duplicate definition for NovaCompute0Passthrough

NovaCompute0Passthrough can be imported with FileInclude from
nova-compute-instance as it is defined there already and makes
use of 'local' params as appropriate.

Change-Id: Id91a0b5780c885bfc8d3d59161c7e3d009af5ae6

commit_message:
haproxy: use SSL on standard SSL ports

The original version of this spec had SSL services running on port
80, which is potentially confusing to deployers expecting that to
be non-SSL.  This proposes a change to the spec to run SSL services
on standard SSL ports (443 in the case of the example here).

Change-Id: I77655a550947533dd8c7cf2be824ddca47319d63

commit_message:
Add Hyper-V driver in the "compute_driver" option description

The description of the option "compute_driver" should include
hyperv.HyperVDriver along with the other supported driver.

Change-Id: Ic7e16fd5154609987b2ef0b6f8ee52619ccf489c
Closes-bug: #1347777

commit_message:
Change URL of the Barbican documentation

Instead of the wiki on Github the developer documentation
of barbican (http://docs.openstack.org/developer/barbican/)
should be used.

Change the reference link from https://github.com/cloudkeep/barbican
to http://docs.openstack.org/developer/barbican/.

Change-Id: I27cac61eb4973bdf6c8f1ec3cd0e8e3fe6f11bb7

(1 comment)

One change (in comment).

Also, as a rule now we require unit tests to accompany changes; someone in IRC can help if you're not experienced writing them. There are examples in the /tests directory."}, {'account_id': 8040, 'date': '2014-07-23 09:19:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2

(2 comments)

Function `package_search` is a bit difficult to understand, but I see no reason to change it in order to allow showing/toggling `is_public` attribute of packages.

Package objects for 'Package definitions' table in muranodashboard are obtained either via this branch https://github.com/stackforge/murano/blob/2014.2.b1/murano/db/catalog/api.py#L258 (for an admin) or via this one https://github.com/stackforge/murano/blob/2014.2.b1/murano/db/catalog/api.py#L265 (for a regular user). In first case, admin would be able to make public package of any user not public, in second case only owner of a package can toggle its public state. So, it should work just fine as it is."}, {'account_id': 12455, 'date': '2014-08-04 17:48:55.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

These changes are not required for is_public functionality'}]

This change, as is, will definitely break backward compatibility. Putting a hold on it for now. We can discuss it further in IRC or weekly Keystone meeting if you prefer. Will remove the -2 if there are no alternatives.

There are multiple ways to reduce the token size already.

1. If you do not need service catalog, just asking Keystone not to return it on token request or validation by specifying the nocatalog query string. For example,

POST /v3/auth/tokens?nocatalog
GET /v3/auth/tokens?nocatalog

2. If you need the entire service catalog but don't want it to be encoded into the PKI token, use UUID token provider.

3. If you only need partial service catalog (i.e. subset of endpoints), use endpoint filtering extension.

4. If you need the entire service catalog but wants to reduce the size of PKI token in general, use either PKIZ or UUID token provider."}, {'account_id': 11708, 'date': '2014-06-05 03:26:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Sorry but no variant is working for me:
1. nocatalog isn't reaaly implemented, and it's brooking horizon and definitively broke nova-to-cinder
2. UUID token are pretty slow on my 1000 node 6 dc, 100 instances/5min setup
4. PKIZ isn't implemented yet, and in fact, it's just temp. solution, because token will be still grow on catalog grow
3. clients needs all endpoints

I started working on it this way because Dolph Mathews mentioned this in their long-term plan. So I'd like to discus it."}, {'account_id': 11708, 'date': '2014-06-05 03:27:36.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
Keystone compact PKI token

Populating service_catalog from admin token if it does not
exists in token. This is controlled by use_admin_service_catalog
parameter, which is could be set to False if you use catalog
filtering.

Change-Id: I6e46af60cd6f9b2b8c16c424dc24bddd9e5a084e
Implements: blueprint compact-pki-token

[{'created': '2014-08-01 19:48:24.000000000', 'message': "Add Desync/Donor states to Pacemaker OCF script

- Increase timeouts for OCF script as we don't need to check every
  minute, HAProxy clustercheck script verifies MySQL every second.
  Even if MySQL got Desync it will be dropped out from HAProxy,
  until it will be Synced.
- Add Donor/Desync to monitor as on slow hardware or when DB is
  large (in production). Monitor function verified only Synced
  state, and terminated mysqld during SST/IST (mysqldump). After
  change OCF should verify states correctly and not to kill mysqld.
  HAProxy relies on clustercheck script waiting for Synced state
  until it adds MySQL node to production.

Change-Id: I0a659c72ab80a33dcdc1c0e26de12c2fd88c75be
Closes-Bug: 1350245
"}, {'created': '2014-08-04 09:14:30.000000000', 'message': "Add Desync/Donor states to Pacemaker OCF script

  minute, HAProxy clustercheck script verifies MySQL every second.

  HAProxy relies on clustercheck script waiting for Synced state
  until it adds MySQL node to production.
- Replace --wsrep-cluster-address=gcomm:// to --wsrep-new-cluster

Closes-Bug: 1350245

commit_message:
Add Desync/Donor states to Pacemaker OCF script

- Increase timeouts for OCF script as we don't need to check every
  minute, HAProxy clustercheck script verifies MySQL every second.
  Even if MySQL got Desync it will be dropped out from HAProxy,
  until it will be Synced.
- Add Donor/Desync to monitor as on slow hardware or when DB is
  large (in production). Monitor function verified only Synced
  state, and terminated mysqld during SST/IST (mysqldump). After
  change OCF should verify states correctly and not to kill mysqld.
  HAProxy relies on clustercheck script waiting for Synced state
  until it adds MySQL node to production.
- Replace --wsrep-cluster-address=gcomm:// to --wsrep-new-cluster

Change-Id: I0a659c72ab80a33dcdc1c0e26de12c2fd88c75be
Closes-Bug: 1350245

of a specific branch from a repo. This change deliberately uses
'master'; a forthcoming change will modify the signature of

commit_message:
Specify 'master' branch in unittest-app

Slugtester is changing to allow the checking out and testing
of a specific branch from a repo. This change deliberately uses
'master'; a forthcoming change will modify the signature of
worker's build and unittest methods to select other branches.

Change-Id: Idf05a9c2faef5b65ff5ea8ac2f8cfb2845a2e02c

commit_message:
Tag test_nova_keypair_resources as gate, not slow

This test doesn't boot any servers (not even cirros) so it can be
a standard gate test.

Change-Id: I73b84816d0fbedb65b395d7bc2ab3644262d898c
Partial-Bug: #1350099

commit_message:
Support assignment for network to DHCP agent

Neutron support to add a network to a DHCP agent and remove one from it.
This will introduce the feature to horizon.

DocImpact

Implements blueprint assignment-network-dhcp-agent

Change-Id: Ia51769851738681ac13bbb7ab9c888e5dfab4370

commit_message:
Handle NotImplementedError in server_diagnostics v3 api

In libvirt driver, it doesn't implement the function of
get_instance_diagnostics().it returns http 500 error No.
we expect http 501 if the function is not implemented.

Change-Id: I59bfaa27b96284bd56917096e0c3fab0d277ba96
Closes-Bug: 1349680

commit_message:
OFAgent: Implement arp responder

This is step 2 implementation of OFAgent l2-population.
This handles an arp packet responding locally to an arp request in such a way
that sends an arp request as a packet-in message to controller and
builds and sends an arp reply packet.
Currently this only supports tunnel.

Implements: blueprint ofagent-l2pop

Change-Id: Ida714f30c0f02c54dda3402c0dbf6047bc182b22

commit_message:
Refactor to remove inheritance in profiles

Inheritance is not necessary and can be replaced with 'require' for
all the profile classes.
According to the Puppet Style Guide Class inheritance is best avoided
if it is not necessary:
http://docs.puppetlabs.com/guides/style_guide.html#class-inheritance

Change-Id: I4149147ec79acac78f2112e4e849bb353df43fa7

Fix a typo.

Fix a trivial typo.  "Check in" is two words.  This is mainly to
trigger the docs to be published to specs.openstack.org.  See this
thread for more info:

http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2014-August/041816.html

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-07-30 10:49:42.000000000', 'message': "Set no quorum policy stop at post deployment

Corosync cluster should being deployed with 'ignore' policy
and puppet ensures that. Later, cluster policy should be updated
to 'stop' (or 'suicide', if fencing enabled) in order to handle
split brain scenarios as appropriate.

Closes-bug: #1348548

commit_message:
Set no quorum policy stop at post deployment

Corosync cluster should being deployed with 'ignore' policy
and puppet ensures that. Later, if there are 3 or more controllers
in cluster, its policy should be updated to 'stop'
(or 'suicide', if fencing enabled) in order to handle split brain
scenarios as appropriate. Otherwise, in case of there are 2 or less
controllers in cluster, qourum policy should not be changed.

Closes-bug: #1348548

Change-Id: Iae2df7736992edcef4ae72f967af9f504d56612b
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Rename Marconi to Zaqar

This patch renames every package, file, match of Marconi in the codebase
to Zaqar *except* for the .gitreview file, which will have to be updated
*after* I8e587af588d9be0b5ebbab4b0f729b106a2ae537 lands.

Implements blueprint: project-rename

Change-Id: I0c82be81f74d022ab609eea8f40ac2c0635374b1

commit_message:
Add simple tests for Mistral CLI

Tests which check basic cli commands:'--help', 'workbook-list',
'execution-list' and 'tasks-list' were added.

Targets blueprint: mistral-cli-integrational-tests

Change-Id: Icb3f195716fb9de4859ac72714b38813ad2a2077

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary error log in cell API

There are unnnecessary error logs in cell API. It tried to log
error for invalid input which is not necessary because we already
raises exception for the bad request.
This patch removes them in both v2/v3 API.

Change-Id: Idd239903aa830f5d8fe50336dfa63a43b617584f
